NAME

  gethostaddr - get IP4 address of a DNS host utility

SYNOPSIS

  gethostaddr (options)

DESCRIPTION

  gethostaddr is a program that will search for the Internet IP4 address of a DNS
  host (or domain).  If the IP4 address is found it will be displayed in standard
  dot notation (nnn.nnn.nnn.nnn).

OPTIONS

  -h <hostname>
  -v print version information and exit
  -? print this usage

